<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Cylindrocladiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cylindrocladiella arbusta" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="arbusta">Cylindrocladiella arbusta</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. natalensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="natalensis">Cy. natalensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. obpyriformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="obpyriformis">Cy. obpyriformis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. parvispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="parvispora">Cy. parvispora</taxonomicName>
. The stipe extensions of 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. arbusta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="arbusta">Cy. arbusta</taxonomicName>
are longer than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. natalensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="natalensis">Cy. natalensis</taxonomicName>
and shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. obpyriformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="obpyriformis">Cy. obpyriformis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. parvispora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="parvispora">Cy. parvispora</taxonomicName>
. Conidia of 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. arbusta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="arbusta">Cy. arbusta</taxonomicName>
are shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. natalensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="natalensis">Cy. natalensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Cy." lsidName="Cy. obpyriformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="obpyriformis">Cy. obpyriformis</taxonomicName>
(Table 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
